I disagree with having the 5 days over 5 months restriction.  I think it would be more applicable to have a single rotation taken away from any guild who breaks this rule, regardless of their postings on the calendar.  If they are not on any rotation, THEN a month of not being able to post of the Rathe Calendar would be fitting.  (Chances are if they are not on any rorations they are small enough to need to Rathe Calendar.)  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hutterr>Hutterr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fallen Shadows</span><br>  Posts: 277<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(8/24/03 10:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=402.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Calandar Crimes and Punishment</span><hr size=1> I disagree with Ray. The punishment should fit the crime to the best of our ability. If they reserve planes quite often (aka more than 5 times in 5 months), then taking away only their planar reservation rights for 1 month is satisfactory. However, if they dont go often, then this really isnt a punishment as it seems unlikely that they would have reserved a plane anyway...hence the entrance of the rotation skip idea.<br>
<br>
I think Rogg is on the right track, but I just cant agree with taking away something that has nothing to do with the crime. It reminds me of a law we have in Ohio that if a deadbeat dad doesnt pay child support, he loses his DRIVERS LISCENSE. Not sure what one has to do with the other, excpet that they dont want to lose their liscense. Just seems like the punishment should either be a static general punishment (like fines and jail IRL) or deal only with the things involved.<br>
<br>
I will support either way though....lot tougher to enforce things in this virtual world than RL hehe. <p>Hutterr Verbruggen<br>
