<br>
Punishments often do not fit the crime; we don't rape rapists, we don't kill murderers (often), we don't steal from thieves. <br>
<br>
Imprisonment is a 'catch all' punishment; and where we move away from the deterrance of a reservations loss for 30 days, I think a general 'catch all' punishment must be the avenue we look at, unfortunately.<br>
<br>
Hopefully the attention drawn to this lately will be enough of a reminder for guilds and people in those guilds, to respect the time of other people, as we'd want our own time respected. <br>
