<br>
1.  Does the guild that infracted loose reservation rights forever on a first time offence?<br>
- I would rather see a time penalty on this rather then &quot;forever&quot; if that is the case.  Guilds change over time and the ones that made the bad judgement call of intruding on another's raid might not be there in a few months.  So maybe a 2 month reservation loss rounding up.  (ex. Infraction happens on Sept 9, they loose the rest of Sept by rounding up and also loose Oct/Nov for the 2 month penalty and can't reserve until December now)<br>
2.  Is there a stated &quot;right way&quot; to take a pickup raid into those reserved planes?<br>
- Such as: You MUST contact an officer from the reserving guild in order to gain permission to raid on a reserved day in these planes.  Any rules set out by those parties on which mobs were &quot;fair game&quot; or not, is up to those parties involved.<br>
3.  About forfeit of rotation mob....what if they have 2 slated on a single day?<br>
-  Would probably want to decide/base that tie breaker on either which one is up more frequently in game (5 day timer vs. 7 day timer) and base it on that.  Or base it on whichever is up more frequently for that guild and penalize the one they won't see as often (6 guilds on Shei, 11 guild on AoW, tie in that would result in forfeit of AoW turn).<br>
<br>
<br>
I'm not really sure how easy it is for those Admins to tally up who's reserved when or any of that stuff, so whatever is easiest for them to police is fine by me.  If you guys want to research the 5 day in 5 month rule that's fine by me.<br>
<br>
I also don't see the Rathe community as being a culture that has alot of this happening on a consistant basis.  A penalty should be in place to just to prevent that thought from crossing anyones mind and I'm sure that whatever is put in place will have a good shot at never being necessary.  So just make it whatever is easiest for the Admin to figure out in case it does happen.<br>
<br>
